column2: jQuery.my is a plugin that binds form controls with js data structures.

column5:
1.2.16

Minor fixes in modal and formgen

1.2.11

Fixes bug preventing modal to close when pivot node is no more in DOM
(removed).

1.0.3

Small bug fixes, now jQuery UI 1.11 compatible.

1.0.0

Added ‘require’ and ‘files’ properties, overall performance
improvements.

0.9.9

Pre-1.0 release. Also several updates at querymy.com.

0.9.8

Added bower.json, bug fixes for lists

0.9.4

$.my came async – init functions can return promise and resolve it when
ready. $(...).my(manifest) now returns promise, which is resolved when
init is finished.

Minor bugfuxes.

JSON-encoded manifests bug in IE8 fixed. Redactor 9.x is now supported.
Sugar 1.4.1 compatible.

0.8.0

Major additions and bugfixes. README.md added.

0.7.2

Added some minor features. Bug fixes.

0.7.0

New init param added. Now $.my can be applied over empty DIV and create
all necessery markup by itself with init function. Different inits can
be applied over entire form and over each of controls.
Select2, Ace and Redactor plugins support added.
Date controls now return strings.
Many other minor changes.

0.5.1

:disabled selector is now understood in css section.

0.5

Bug fixes, added support of CLEditor, nested forms and possibility to
add/modify form controls at runtime.

0.4 beta release

Huge optimization, bug fix and compatibility recheck.

0.3 beta release

Undo and jQuery UI basic support are added. Several bug fixes for
input[type=button].
